    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-08-25T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-08-25T14:00:00-05:00" n="162"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d162">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3731/1008a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Matthews</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-25T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 25, 1934—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>181. Upon the trade agreement becoming effective, it will then be the controlling
                    basis for the trade relations between the United States and Cuba. While it is
                    not necessary that the decree law correspond exactly with the text of the
                    agreement, in so far as detailed nomenclature is concerned, it is essential that
                    the two instruments be in substantial agreement.<note n="73" xml:id="d162fn73"
                        >For text of decree law No. 440, August 24, 1934, see <hi rend="italic"
                            >Gaceta Oficial de la República de Cuba</hi>, August 24, 1934,
                        Extraordinary Edition No. 76.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Inasmuch as the exchange of notes on pineapple slips took place yesterday, in
                    order to make effective the lifting of the embargo, it would appear to be
                    necessary for a decree law to revoke or amend the present export prohibition,
                    contained in item 7, provision 5, for the application of the tariff.<note n="74"
                        xml:id="d162fn74">For text of decree law No. 453, August 28, 1934, lifting
                        the embargo on pineapple slips, see <hi rend="italic">Gaceta Oficial</hi>,
                        August 29, 1934.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
